            <h1 class="text-center">Who are we?</h1>

            <img src="img/About-Us-1024x463.jpg" class="center">

            <h2 class="text-center">Mission Statement</h2>

            <p>"To provide a fun, realistic and authentic Australian ArmA MILSIM experience whilst building a fair,
                persistent and active community of mature gamers."</p>

            <h3 class="text-center">Our Vision</h3>

            <p>SOCOMD, as an ArmA III gaming community, aims to provide members with the most authentic Australian
                MILSIM experience by emulating the organisational structure, training methods and planning procedures
                utilised by actual military forces. Every member will be proficiently trained, according to their rank,
                to follow standard operating procedures that are realistic, adjusted for ArmA III and have been reviewed
                by former military personnel.</p>

            <h3 class="text-center">Who are We?</h3>

            <p>Special Operations Command (SOCOMD) is an Australian based ArmA realism unit that is structured around
                the Commando Regiment of the Australian Defence Force. SOCOMD specialises largely in COOP, with the
                exception of some TvT, ArmA gameplay, utilising equipment, strategies and tactics based on those
                employed by the Australian Military.</p>

            <p>In other words, we don't refer to each other by our ranks or salute the Officers amongst us when we are
                in-game but we do hold it in high regard and respect, following these customs is purely optional. We do
                however, pride ourselves on maintaining a fun, immersive and authentic ArmA gaming experience - yes,
                this means that good old fashioned Aussie banter is welcome, but when the bullets start flying, it's
                time to get our A-Game on.</p>

            <p>With SOCOMD's founder being a former member of the RAAF's Airfield Defence Guards (ADG's), and other
                members having either served previously or are currently serving in the Australian Defence Force, this
                is the unit for you if you want an immersive and authentic Australian ArmA gaming experience. Head over
                to our media section to get a feel for what we are about, and what it is like to play ArmA with
                us.</p>
        </div>
